<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Purple Wiggle Lachlan Gillespie and his ballet dancer fiancée Dana Stephensen surprised fans when they welcomed twins last week. </p>

<p>And on Friday, the mother-of-three reflected on bringing newborn daughters Lulu and Lottie into the world. </p>

<p>Dana, 34, posted a sweet picture of herself to Instagram cradling their babies on her chest after giving birth, saying it was 'one of the most amazing experiences.' </p>

<p> 'It was one of the most amazing experiences': On Friday, Lachlan Gillespie's fiancée Dana Stephensen shared a sweet image of herself cradling their twins after giving birth</p>

<p>'One of the most amazing experiences bringing our girls into the world. Doubly blessed,' she captioned the post. </p>

<p>Dana also posted a photo of her son Jasper, four, who she shares with her photographer ex-husband, Michael Kai.</p>

<p>'And to the most beautiful little boy who made me a mummy - I adore you,' she captioned the post. </p>

<p>He has two little sisters now! Dana also posted a photo of her son Jasper, four, who she shares with her photographer ex-husband, Michael Kai</p>

<p>Shock arrival! The couple surprised fans when they welcomed twins last week</p>

<p>Last week, Dana and Lachlan surprised fans when they announced they had welcomed twins, having kept the pregnancy under wraps. </p>

<p>In an Instagram post, Lachlan, 34, shared a photo of his newborn daughters resting with their mother Dana, 34, as he looked on lovingly. </p>

<p>He wrote in the caption: 'Oh Lulu and Lottie, your mummy and daddy love you with all we have - you are both so beautiful - and I would love to sing to you both forever'. </p>

<p>Neither Lachlan nor Dana gave any hint that they were expecting, and their social media accounts do not show many recent photos.   </p>

<p>Still friends: Lachlan's ex-wife Emma Watkins (pictured), who is the Yellow Wiggle, and a number of other celebrities wished the couple congratulations</p>

<p>Sweet: The Yellow Wiggle kept it simple posting two purple love heart emoji's in the comments</p>

<p>Lachlan's ex-wife Emma Watkins, who is the Yellow Wiggle, and a number of other celebrities wished the couple congratulations. </p>

<p>Lachlan and Dana announced the happy news on Instagram, prompting Emma to post two purple love heart emoji's in the comments. </p>

<p>Meanwhile, musical theatre star Lucy Durak, 37, wrote: 'Oh Lachy! The hugest congratulations to you and Dana and your beautiful family.' </p>

<p>Red Wiggle Simon Pryce, 48, commented: 'So beautiful. Congratulations.'  </p>

<p>In addition, television presenter Melissa Doyle, 50, also sent her well wishes writing: 'Bless! Such wonderful news. Much love to all of you.' </p>

<p>Comedian Em Rusciano, 41, also congratulated the couple saying: 'Oh how wonderful.' </p>

<p>Celeb comments: Following the joyous news, the couple have been inundated with well-wishes from a number of Australian celebrities, including Lucy Durak, Melissa Doyle and Simon Pryce</p>

<p>The couple announced their engagement in April in a sweet Instagram post, with Lachy writing: 'On Thursday night, Dana asked me to marry her at home under a fairy light sky and a very excited little boy in a beautiful bow tie.' </p>

<p>In the photo, Lachlan was pictured cuddling up to Dana and Dana's son Jasper, four, inside a bedroom festooned with fairy lights. </p>

<p>The couple, who went public with their relationship in October, beamed with joy as they cuddled up for the milestone photo. </p>

<p>Lachlan separated from his Wiggles bandmate Emma Watkins (a.k.a. The Yellow Wiggle) in August 2018, after two years of marriage.  </p>

<p>Congratulations: Lachy announced his engagement to ballet dancer Dana after she proposed to him at home in April. Pictured with Jasper - Dana's four-year-old son from a previous relationship </p>

